# Example environment configuration for aws-cockpit-outpost
# Copy this file to .env and update with your values
# AWS Configuration - Replace with your actual values
OUTPOST_ID=op-0123456789abcdef0
SUBNET_ID=subnet-0123456789abcdef0
SECURITY_GROUP_ID=sg-0123456789abcdef0
KEY_NAME=your-key-pair-name
INSTANCE_TYPE=c6id.metal
REGION=us-east-1


# Self-Contained Deployment Notes:
# - Complete Cockpit installation happens via user-data bootstrap script
# - No SSM documents required - everything is self-contained
# - Installation includes: core Cockpit, virtualization, containers, monitoring, file management
# - Default users created: admin/rocky (password: Cockpit123)
# - Total deployment time: ~20-30 minutes on Outpost instances
# Usage:
# 1. Copy this file: cp .env.example .env
# 2. Edit .env with your actual AWS configuration values
# 3. Run: ./launch-cockpit-instance.sh